    "content": "**Code Explanation:**\n\nThe code performs the requested data cleaning and feature engineering steps on the ABO3 Perovskite Dataset. First, it loads the raw dataset and prints the initial shape, missing values, and numerical distributions. It then drops the specified columns (`surface_energy`, `work_function`, `A_period`, `B_period`, `theoretical`) along with any duplicate columns (identified by the `.1` suffix). The `material_id` column is set as the DataFrame index. \n\nNext, it applies a `log1p` transformation to `volume` and `elastic_anisotropy` to handle their right-skewed distributions, renaming them to `log_volume` and `log_elastic_anisotropy`. Three new features are engineered: `abs_tau_diff` (absolute deviation of the tolerance factor from the ideal 1.0), `radius_diff` (difference between A-site and B-site atomic radii), and `ie_ratio` (ratio of their first ionization energies). The `radius_ratio` column is dropped to prevent multicollinearity with `tau`. A boolean column `is_elastic_characterized` is created to flag the 215 materials that have computed bulk moduli (`K_VRH`). \n\nFinally, the code prints the updated summary statistics and the exact counts of the full dataset versus the elastic subset, before saving the cleaned dataset to `data/cleaned_perovskite_data.csv`. String concatenation is used for all print statements to comply with the formatting constraints.\n\n**Python Code:**\n\n```python\nimport pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport os\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    # Set pandas display options to avoid truncation\n    pd.set_option('display.max_rows', None)\n    pd.set_option('display.max_columns', None)\n    pd.set_option('display.width', 1000)\n    \n    # Define paths\n    input_path = \"/home/node/work/projects/materials_project_v3/perovskite_data.csv\"\n    output_dir = \"data/\"\n    output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, \"cleaned_perovskite_data.csv\")\n    \n    # Load data\n    df = pd.read_csv(input_path)\n    \n    print(\"========================================\")\n    print(\"--- BEFORE CLEANING ---\")\n    print(\"========================================\")\n    print(\"Shape: \" + str(df.shape))\n    print(\"\\nMissing values per column:\")\n    missing_before = df.isnull().sum()\n    print(missing_before[missing_before > 0].sort_values(ascending=False))\n    \n    print(\"\\nDistributions (numerical columns):\")\n    print(df.describe().T[['count', 'mean', 'std', 'min', '50%', 'max']])\n    \n    # 1. Remove columns\n    cols_to_drop = ['surface_energy', 'work_function', 'A_period', 'B_period', 'theoretical']\n    df = df.drop(columns=[col for col in cols_to_drop if col in df.columns])\n    \n    # Remove duplicate columns (e.g., ending with .1)\n    duplicate_cols = [col for col in df.columns if col.endswith('.1')]\n    df = df.drop(columns=duplicate_cols)\n    \n    # 2. Set material_id as index\n    if 'material_id' in df.columns:\n        df = df.set_index('material_id')\n        \n    # 3. Apply log-transformation to volume and elastic_anisotropy\n    if 'volume' in df.columns:\n        df['log_volume'] = np.log1p(df['volume'])\n        df = df.drop(columns=['volume'])\n    if 'elastic_anisotropy' in df.columns:\n        df['log_elastic_anisotropy'] = np.log1p(df['elastic_anisotropy'].clip(lower=0))\n        df = df.drop(columns=['elastic_anisotropy'])\n        \n    # 4. Engineer features\n    if 'tau' in df.columns:\n        df['abs_tau_diff'] = np.abs(df['tau'] - 1.0)\n    if 'A_radius' in df.columns and 'B_radius' in df.columns:\n        df['radius_diff'] = df['A_radius'] - df['B_radius']\n    if 'A_ie1' in df.columns and 'B_ie1' in df.columns:\n        df['ie_ratio'] = df['A_ie1'] / df['B_ie1']\n        \n    # 5. Drop radius_ratio\n    if 'radius_ratio' in df.columns:\n        df = df.drop(columns=['radius_ratio'])\n        \n    # 6. Create boolean column is_elastic_characterized\n    if 'K_VRH' in df.columns:\n        df['is_elastic_characterized'] = df['K_VRH'].notnull()\n        \n    print(\"\\n========================================\")\n    print(\"--- AFTER CLEANING ---\")\n    print(\"========================================\")\n    print(\"Shape: \" + str(df.shape))\n    print(\"\\nMissing values per column:\")\n    missing_after = df.isnull().sum()\n    print(missing_after[missing_after > 0].sort_values(ascending=False))\n    \n    print(\"\\nDistributions (numerical columns):\")\n    print(df.describe().T[['count', 'mean', 'std', 'min', '50%', 'max']])\n    \n    # 8. Print counts\n    full_count = len(df)\n    elastic_count = df['is_elastic_characterized'].sum()\n    print(\"\\n========================================\")\n    print(\"--- DATASET COUNTS ---\")\n    print(\"========================================\")\n    print(\"Total rows in full dataset: \" + str(full_count))\n    print(\"Rows in elastic subset (characterized): \" + str(elastic_count))\n    \n    # 9. Save cleaned dataset\n    df.to_csv(output_path)\n    print(\"\\nCleaned dataset saved to \" + output_path)\n```",
